{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17592461","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17592461"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-30T10:14:47+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-30T10:14:47+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"15251"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"15251","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/15251"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"7942"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"65969"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"7942","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/7942"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"15251"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"51418"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"19"},{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"74"},{"type":"tags","id":"581"},{"type":"tags","id":"2058"},{"type":"tags","id":"4928"},{"type":"tags","id":"4937"},{"type":"tags","id":"4946"},{"type":"tags","id":"4950"},{"type":"tags","id":"7662"},{"type":"tags","id":"8127"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"19338"},{"type":"contributions","id":"19341"},{"type":"contributions","id":"22049"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"65969","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/65969"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EThe photograph shows a tumour of the parotid gland under high magnification (Image). The specimen demonstrates a well-circumscribed lesion with both epithelial and mesenchymal elements. There are ductal structures lined by cuboidal cells embedded in a chondromyxoid stroma containing spindle-shaped myoepithelial cells.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following is the most likely diagnosis?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Adenoid cystic carcinoma","Basal cell adenoma","Mucoepidermoid carcinoma","Pleomorphic adenoma","Warthin tumour"],"correctOptions":[3],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThe histological features are characteristic of a \u003Cstrong\u003Epleomorphic adenoma\u003C/strong\u003E, which is the most common benign tumour of the salivary glands. The key diagnostic features include the presence of both epithelial and mesenchymal elements with a chondromyxoid stroma.\u003C/p\u003E        \u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EAdenoid cystic carcinoma\u003C/strong\u003E typically shows a cribriform pattern with multiple cylindrical spaces. \u003Cstrong\u003EWarthin tumour\u003C/strong\u003E demonstrates prominent lymphoid tissue with germinal centres and oncocytic epithelium. \u003Cstrong\u003EMucoepidermoid carcinoma\u003C/strong\u003E shows a mixture of mucous, intermediate and epidermoid cells without chondromyxoid stroma. \u003Cstrong\u003EBasal cell adenoma\u003C/strong\u003E consists of basaloid cells arranged in solid, trabecular, or tubular patterns without mesenchymal elements.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["Pleomorphic adenoma is the most common benign tumor of the parotid gland, characterised by mixed epithelial and mesenchymal elements.","Histologically, pleomorphic adenoma shows a mixture of epithelial cells in ductal patterns and myoepithelial cells in a chondromyxoid stroma."],"references":["\u0022Pleomorphic_adenoma\u0022 by KGH is CC BY-SA 3.0, https://commons.wikimedia.org/w/index.php?curid=559289","Mantsopoulos K, Thimsen V, Gostian AO, M\u00fcller SK, Sievert M, Iro AK, Agaimy A, Iro H. Histopathology of Parotid Pleomorphic Adenomas: A \u0022Pleomorphic Approach\u0022 to a Demanding Lesion. Laryngoscope. 2022 Jan;132(1):73-77. doi: 10.1002/lary.29726. Epub 2021 Jul 2. PMID: 34213780.","Bokhari MR, Greene J. Pleomorphic Adenoma. [Updated 2023 Jul 4]. In: StatPearls [Internet]. Treasure Island (FL): StatPearls Publishing; 2024 Jan-. Available from: https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/books/NBK430829/","Yamada, T., Alpers, D. H., Kalloo, A. N., Kaplowitz, N., Owyang, C., \u0026 Powell, D. W. (Eds.). (2011). Textbook of gastroenterology. John Wiley \u0026 Sons","Kumar, V., Abbas, A. K., \u0026 Aster, J. C. (Eds.). (2012). Robbins basic pathology e-book. Elsevier Health Science"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"51418"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"15251"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[{"type":"media","id":"21138"}]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"media","id":"21138","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/media/21138"},"attributes":{"mimeType":"image/jpeg","url":"https://app.emedici.com/storage/media/S3GfM5HLFFLATXsn3hTRRq8j7RXPIy.jpg","thumbUrl":"https://app.emedici.com/storage/media/S3GfM5HLFFLATXsn3hTRRq8j7RXPIy.jpg","isProcessed":true,"width":600,"height":452}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"51418","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/51418"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2024-11-28T10:57:13+10:30","updatedAt":"2024-11-28T10:57:30+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"7942"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"65969"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"19","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/19"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83d\udd2a","name":"General Surgery","synonyms":[],"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":"2024-11-21T09:47:20+10:30"},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"1"}},"heading":{"data":{"type":"tagHeadings","id":"2"}}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"67","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/67"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Basic Science","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null